tldr: The user requested to add a database and admin dashboard to a sleep
  questionnaire application. The assistant implemented a PostgreSQL database
  with Prisma, API routes for data storage and CSV export, and a simple
  password-protected admin dashboard, later refactoring the authentication to
  use Next.js middleware for a cleaner solution.
overview: The user's intent was to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by
  adding persistent data storage and an administrative interface. The approach
  involved integrating a PostgreSQL database (NeonDB) using Prisma for schema
  management and data operations. Key decisions included using a simple
  password-based authentication system for the admin dashboard and later
  refactoring it to leverage Next.js middleware for more efficient route
  protection. The implementation covered updating demographic data fields,
  creating a Prisma model for questionnaire responses, developing API endpoints
  for data submission, retrieval, and CSV export, and building a functional
  admin login page and dashboard. Despite initial minor hiccups during
  browser-based form submission testing, direct API calls and subsequent browser
  tests confirmed all database and authentication functionalities were working
  as expected.
